---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ShareButtons from '../../../components/ShareButtons.astro';
import NextEpisodeTeaser from '../../../components/NextEpisodeTeaser.astro';

const codeExample = `<span class="text-cyan">from</span> deepagents <span class="text-cyan">import</span> create_deep_agent
<span class="text-cyan">from</span> langchain_openai <span class="text-cyan">import</span> ChatOpenAI

agent = create_deep_agent(
    model=ChatOpenAI(model=<span class="text-green">"gpt-4o"</span>),
    tools=[web_search, code_executor],
    system_prompt=<span class="text-green">"You are a research expert."</span>,
)

<span class="text-text-muted"># Planning, file system, sub-agents, memory - all built in.</span>
result = <span class="text-cyan">await</span> agent.ainvoke({
    <span class="text-green">"messages"</span>: [{<span class="text-green">"role"</span>: <span class="text-green">"user"</span>, <span class="text-green">"content"</span>: <span class="text-green">"Research quantum computing breakthroughs in 2026"</span>}]
})`;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="What are LangChain Deep Agents? | Demystifying AI in 5 Minutes"
  description="LangChain shipped Deep Agents - an opinionated agent harness that bundles planning, file systems, sub-agents, and memory on top of LangGraph. Here's the 3-layer stack that changes everything."
  image="/og-series-ep01-deep-agents.png"
  keywords="LangChain Deep Agents, LangGraph, Agent Harness, AI Agents, Sub-Agents, TodoList Middleware, Virtual File System, Agent Memory, create_deep_agent, Agentic AI"
  publishedDate="2026-07-06"
>

  <style>
    .layer-card {
      transition: all 0.3s ease;
    }
    .layer-card:hover {
      transform: translateX(4px);
    }
    .superpower-card {
      transition: all 0.3s ease;
    }
    .superpower-card:hover {
      transform: translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(63, 185, 80, 0.1);
    }
    .code-block {
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .vs-card {
      transition: all 0.3s ease;
    }
    .vs-card:hover {
      transform: scale(1.01);
    }
  </style>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden border-b border-border">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-green/[0.04] via-background to-background"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(ellipse_at_top,rgba(63,185,80,0.06)_0%,transparent_60%)]"></div>

    <div class="relative container-main max-w-4xl pt-20 pb-10">
      <a href="/series/demystifying-ai" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-secondary hover:text-green transition-colors mb-8 font-mono">
        <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18"/></svg>
        cd ~/series/demystifying-ai
      </a>

      <!-- Hero Image -->
      <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-border mb-8">
        <img src="/series/ep01-deep-agents.png" alt="Deep Agents Architecture - 3-layer stack with Planning, FileSystem, Sub-Agents, and Memory" class="w-full h-auto" />
      </div>

      <!-- Meta -->
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[10px] text-green font-mono bg-green/5 border border-green/20 px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-green animate-pulse"></span>
          EPISODE 01
        </span>
        <span class="px-2.5 py-1 text-[10px] font-mono bg-green/10 border border-green/20 text-green rounded-full">Hot Topic</span>
        <span class="text-[10px] text-secondary font-mono">Jul 6, 2026</span>
        <span class="text-[10px] text-secondary font-mono">5 min read</span>
      </div>

      <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-foreground leading-tight mb-3">
        What are LangChain Deep Agents?
      </h1>
      <p class="text-base text-secondary max-w-2xl mb-5">
        LangChain shipped something that makes CrewAI and AutoGen look like toys. Nobody noticed. Here's the 3-layer stack that changes everything.
      </p>

      <ShareButtons title="What are LangChain Deep Agents?" url="/series/demystifying-ai/deep-agents" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Article Body -->
  <article class="container-main max-w-4xl py-10">

    <!-- TLDR -->
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-green/20 bg-green/[0.03] p-6 mb-10 max-w-3xl">
      <span class="text-xs font-mono text-green font-bold">// TL;DR</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-foreground/90 leading-relaxed mt-3 mb-0">
        <strong>Deep Agents</strong> = LangGraph + planning + file system + sub-agents + memory. One <code class="text-green bg-green/10 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">create_deep_agent()</code> call. Production-ready out of the box.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- The Problem: Visual Comparison -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-green font-mono text-sm">#</span> Shallow vs Deep
      </h2>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <!-- Shallow Agent -->
        <div class="vs-card rounded-xl border border-red-500/20 bg-red-500/[0.02] p-5">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-red-500/10 border border-red-500/20 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-red-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-bold text-red-400">Shallow Agent</span>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-2.5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-secondary">
              <span class="text-red-400/60">&#10005;</span> Forgets after 5 steps
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-secondary">
              <span class="text-red-400/60">&#10005;</span> No planning capability
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-secondary">
              <span class="text-red-400/60">&#10005;</span> Context window fills up
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-secondary">
              <span class="text-red-400/60">&#10005;</span> Single-threaded execution
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-secondary">
              <span class="text-red-400/60">&#10005;</span> No cross-session memory
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4 pt-3 border-t border-red-500/10">
            <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-red-400/60">LLM + tools in a loop</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Deep Agent -->
        <div class="vs-card rounded-xl border border-green/20 bg-green/[0.02] p-5">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-green/10 border border-green/20 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-green" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-bold text-green">Deep Agent</span>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-2.5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-secondary">
              <span class="text-green">&#10003;</span> Coherent over 200+ steps
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-secondary">
              <span class="text-green">&#10003;</span> Built-in todo planning
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-secondary">
              <span class="text-green">&#10003;</span> Virtual file system offloads context
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-secondary">
              <span class="text-green">&#10003;</span> Parallel sub-agent delegation
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-secondary">
              <span class="text-green">&#10003;</span> Persistent memory across sessions
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4 pt-3 border-t border-green/10">
            <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-green/60">Same loop + 4 superpowers</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-secondary mt-4">
        Claude Code, Manus, and Deep Research all use this pattern. <strong class="text-foreground">Deep Agents packages it into a library.</strong>
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- The 3-Layer Stack -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-green font-mono text-sm">#</span> The 3-Layer Stack
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-secondary mb-6">Not a replacement for LangGraph. A layer on top. All three compose.</p>

      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div class="layer-card rounded-lg border border-green/30 bg-green/[0.05] p-4 pl-5 border-l-4 border-l-green">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-green font-bold px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-green/10 rounded">L3</span>
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground">Deep Agents</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-xs text-secondary mt-1 mb-0">Full harness. Planning + FS + sub-agents + memory. Start here.</p>
            </div>
            <code class="text-[10px] font-mono text-green/60 shrink-0 ml-4 hidden sm:block">create_deep_agent()</code>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="layer-card rounded-lg border border-cyan/30 bg-cyan/[0.03] p-4 pl-5 border-l-4 border-l-cyan">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-cyan font-bold px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-cyan/10 rounded">L2</span>
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground">create_agent</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-xs text-secondary mt-1 mb-0">Minimal ReAct loop. Model + tools = working agent.</p>
            </div>
            <code class="text-[10px] font-mono text-cyan/60 shrink-0 ml-4 hidden sm:block">create_react_agent()</code>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="layer-card rounded-lg border border-violet-500/30 bg-violet-500/[0.03] p-4 pl-5 border-l-4 border-l-violet-500">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-violet-400 font-bold px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-violet-500/10 rounded">L1</span>
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground">LangGraph</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-xs text-secondary mt-1 mb-0">Raw graph runtime. Full control over everything.</p>
            </div>
            <code class="text-[10px] font-mono text-violet-400/60 shrink-0 ml-4 hidden sm:block">StateGraph()</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- The 4 Superpowers -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-green font-mono text-sm">#</span> The 4 Superpowers
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-secondary mb-6">Auto-injected middleware. You get all four with zero config.</p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="superpower-card rounded-xl border border-border bg-elevated p-5">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5 mb-3">
            <div class="w-9 h-9 rounded-lg bg-green/10 border border-green/20 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2M9 5a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2M9 5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2m-6 9l2 2 4-4"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-foreground">Planning</h3>
              <p class="text-[10px] text-green font-mono">write_todos tool</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-secondary mb-0">
            Agent creates and checks off tasks. Stays focused across 50+ steps. Same pattern as Claude Code.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="superpower-card rounded-xl border border-border bg-elevated p-5">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5 mb-3">
            <div class="w-9 h-9 rounded-lg bg-cyan/10 border border-cyan/20 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-cyan" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 7v10a2 2 0 002 2h14a2 2 0 002-2V9a2 2 0 00-2-2h-6l-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-foreground">Virtual File System</h3>
              <p class="text-[10px] text-cyan font-mono">read/write with permissions</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-secondary mb-0">
            Offloads large results. Stores artifacts. Context window never blows up.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="superpower-card rounded-xl border border-border bg-elevated p-5">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5 mb-3">
            <div class="w-9 h-9 rounded-lg bg-violet-500/10 border border-violet-500/20 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-violet-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-foreground">Sub-Agents</h3>
              <p class="text-[10px] text-violet-400 font-mono">isolated context workers</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-secondary mb-0">
            Delegate tasks to parallel workers. They run isolated, return results. Parent context stays clean.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="superpower-card rounded-xl border border-border bg-elevated p-5">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5 mb-3">
            <div class="w-9 h-9 rounded-lg bg-yellow-500/10 border border-yellow-500/20 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-yellow-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9.663 17h4.673M12 3v1m6.364 1.636l-.707.707M21 12h-1M4 12H3m3.343-5.657l-.707-.707m2.828 9.9a5 5 0 117.072 0l-.548.547A3.374 3.374 0 0014 18.469V19a2 2 0 11-4 0v-.531c0-.895-.356-1.754-.988-2.386l-.548-.547z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-foreground">Long-term Memory</h3>
              <p class="text-[10px] text-yellow-400 font-mono">LangGraph Store</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-secondary mb-0">
            Remembers preferences and decisions across sessions. Gets better with every use.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Markdown is the Brain -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-green font-mono text-sm">#</span> .md Files Are the Brain
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-secondary mb-6">The real config layer isn't Python or YAML. It's plain markdown.</p>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-elevated overflow-hidden">
        <!-- Visual header -->
        <div class="p-4 border-b border-border bg-green/[0.02]">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
              <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded bg-green/20 border border-green/30"></div>
              <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-green">CLAUDE.md</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
              <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded bg-cyan/20 border border-cyan/30"></div>
              <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-cyan">AGENTS.md</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
              <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded bg-violet-500/20 border border-violet-500/30"></div>
              <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-violet-400">rules/*.md</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
              <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded bg-yellow-500/20 border border-yellow-500/30"></div>
              <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-yellow-400">skills/*.md</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Grid of what lives in md -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 divide-x divide-y divide-border">
          <div class="p-4 text-center">
            <div class="text-lg mb-1">&#128221;</div>
            <span class="text-[10px] font-bold text-foreground block">System Prompt</span>
            <span class="text-[9px] text-secondary">Core instructions</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 text-center">
            <div class="text-lg mb-1">&#9889;</div>
            <span class="text-[10px] font-bold text-foreground block">Skills</span>
            <span class="text-[9px] text-secondary">On-demand capabilities</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 text-center">
            <div class="text-lg mb-1">&#128218;</div>
            <span class="text-[10px] font-bold text-foreground block">Rules</span>
            <span class="text-[9px] text-secondary">Guardrails &amp; constraints</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 text-center">
            <div class="text-lg mb-1">&#129504;</div>
            <span class="text-[10px] font-bold text-foreground block">Memory</span>
            <span class="text-[9px] text-secondary">Learned preferences</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 text-center">
            <div class="text-lg mb-1">&#128203;</div>
            <span class="text-[10px] font-bold text-foreground block">Plans</span>
            <span class="text-[9px] text-secondary">Task strategies</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 text-center">
            <div class="text-lg mb-1">&#127919;</div>
            <span class="text-[10px] font-bold text-foreground block">Context</span>
            <span class="text-[9px] text-secondary">Domain knowledge</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Punchline -->
        <div class="p-4 border-t border-border bg-green/[0.02]">
          <p class="text-xs text-foreground/90 m-0 text-center">
            <strong>Change the markdown, change the agent.</strong> No redeployment. No code changes. Just edit a file.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-dashed border-green/20 p-3 bg-green/[0.01]">
        <p class="text-xs text-secondary m-0">
          <strong class="text-foreground">Key insight:</strong> If you can write a README, you can program a production agent. The .md files <em>are</em> the agent.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Code Example -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-green font-mono text-sm">#</span> 5 Lines to Start
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-secondary mb-4">Everything else is handled by the harness.</p>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-[#0d1117] overflow-hidden">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2.5 border-b border-border bg-elevated/50">
          <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-red-500/60"></span>
          <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-yellow-500/60"></span>
          <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-green/60"></span>
          <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-secondary ml-2">main.py</span>
        </div>
        <pre class="code-block p-5 overflow-x-auto text-secondary"><Fragment set:html={codeExample} /></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- When to Use What -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-green font-mono text-sm">#</span> Pick Your Layer
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-secondary mb-4">Start at the top. Drop down only when needed.</p>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border overflow-hidden">
        <table class="w-full text-xs">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-border bg-elevated/50">
              <th class="text-left p-3 font-mono text-green">You need...</th>
              <th class="text-left p-3 font-mono text-green">Use this</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-secondary">
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="p-3">Quick chatbot, single tool</td>
              <td class="p-3"><code class="text-cyan bg-cyan/10 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">create_agent</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="p-3 font-medium text-foreground">Research, code gen, multi-step work</td>
              <td class="p-3"><code class="text-green bg-green/10 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-bold">Deep Agents</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="p-3">Custom control flow, complex branching</td>
              <td class="p-3"><code class="text-violet-400 bg-violet-500/10 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">LangGraph</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-3">Both: harness + custom sub-graph</td>
              <td class="p-3"><code class="text-yellow-400 bg-yellow-500/10 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">Compose them</code></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Bottom Line -->
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-green/20 bg-green/[0.03] p-6 max-w-3xl mb-10">
      <span class="text-xs font-mono text-green font-bold">// Bottom Line</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-foreground/90 leading-relaxed mt-3 mb-0">
        Deep Agents is what happens when you package the Claude Code architecture into a library. <strong>Planning, file system, sub-agents, memory.</strong> One pip install. If you're building anything beyond a wrapper, this is your starting point in 2026.
      </p>
    </div>

    <NextEpisodeTeaser current={1} />

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mt-10 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-4 p-5 rounded-xl border border-border bg-elevated">
